snippet.textDisplay:
Oh Shaq... you are the man!
Respect on top of respect, and that's because, first, he was a son, a brother, an uncle and a cousin, then ALL the things everybody else said. Shaq did hus speech in a way where not even vanessa can be made. So tasteful and mature!

Another thing that pissed me off was the PowerPoint slide that was rolling that said: Forever.... throughout the whole service I was just hoping it said son forever and brother forever.... but it didn't. I was hoping pictures were included of his sisters and the few of his parents, cuz let's face it there are many pictures out there online and not one was included. We do not know the full issues surrounding this family but I was still hoping that those significant parts of Kobes life were documented, but they weren't.
Hopefully the death and grief brings vannessa and his sisters together and then hopefully that will create the path for the grandparents to enter vannessa and the children's lives.

May God bless them all. Dysfunction and toxicity within families is the worst thing ever.

snippet.textDisplay:
4:50 this is why eulogies are vanity. Eulogies are done to comfort those left behind and have no other benefit. A eulogy does nothing for the departed, who cannot hear the it but are designed to make the listener feel better about themselves when they should be seriously thinking about their own death and what they will face on the other side.
Playing basketball in heaven?
Resting in peace?
See you again?
All of these statements are purely wishful thinking, unless this guy has some divine knowledge.
Did Bryant or his daughter ever profess faith in Christ?
If not, then one thing is for certain; they are not together, not playing anything and certainly not at peace.
There is no peace apart from Christ and there is no way to heaven but through Christ.
People: pick up a bible and read it. Pray to the God of Abraham and Isaac and Jacob and repent of your sins, calling upon the name of Jesus declaring Him to be Lord and savior.
All who call upon the LORD with a contrite heart will be saved.
Those who die apart from Christ will not saved and will enter into an etetnity of condemnation.

Throw down your jewels and suits and fast cars, your comfortable living and self righteousness and humble yourself before Almighty God Who is the judge of all the earth but also the Justifier of those who take refuge in Him through His Son the Lord Jesus Christ.
